<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-318-642  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 318 642.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  April 9 1990 n1402* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sony, Scientific Atlanta, Mast claim first high definition TVconference. (MAST Industries Inc.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sony Corporation of America (products)Scientific-Atlanta Inc. (products)Mast Industries (communication systems).andO;Ticker:    SFA.andO;Topic:     High-Definition TelevisionVideoconferencingFashion Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SONY, SCIENTIFIC ATLANTA, MAST CLAIM FIRST HIGHandM;DEFINITION TV CONFERENCEandM;Sony Corp of America, Scientific-Atlanta Inc and MAST Industries Inc haveco-operatively accomplished what they are proudly calling the world's firstHigh Definition Television videoconference, by linking Andover,Massachusetts-based MASTIndustries, the design and procurement arm of USretail group The Limited Inc, with Hong Kong fashion manufacturers.andP;  As awhole, the transmission involved two satellite hops and three fibre opticlinks in two directions, simultaneously using HDB-MAC all the way.andP;  The HongKong feed was accomplished via cable TV and satellite-based communicationsnetwork supplier Scientific-Atlanta's HDB-MAC satellite transmission systemtransmitting over fibre optic lines within Hong Kong, with the feed thenuplinked to an Intelsat satellite over the Pacific.andP;  From that satellite, thesignal went via an ATandamp;T ground station in the Pacific Northwest to a GEAmericom satellite across the US, going directly to MAST headquarters inAndover.andP;  A similar path carried the return signal back to Hong Kong.andP;  Sonyhigh-definition cameras, monitors, and projection equipment was installed inMAST offices in Hong Kong and Andover, so that MAST buyers could study thefabrics being displayed.andP;  Santa Monica, California-based Vision Accomplisheddesigned the network, while both Cable andamp; Wireless Hong Kong and Hong KongTelephone provided the Hong Kong fibre-optic links.andO;</TEXT></DOC>